## `/teamspace` ‚Äî Process TeamSpace Check-In

When the user types **`/teamspace`** or **`/teamspace [name]`**, process a pasted TeamSpace check-in and extract relevant information.

### Input Formats

| Format | Example |
|--------|---------|
| Trigger then paste | `/teamspace` followed by pasted check-in |
| With name specified | `/teamspace Dustin` then paste |
| Multiple check-ins | `/teamspace all` then paste batch |

### Processing Flow

#### Step 1: Identify Team Member

If name not specified, prompt:
```
üìã TEAMSPACE CHECK-IN

Who is this check-in from?
(Match to people.md or specify new name)
```

If name provided, match against `private/context/people.md`:
- First name match (case-insensitive)
- Flag if unknown: "I don't have [Name] in people.md. Add them?"

#### Step 2: Extract Check-In Components

Parse the TeamSpace format for these sections:

| Section | What to Extract | Maps To |
|---------|-----------------|---------|
| **Enjoyed Last Week** | What they liked working on | 1:1 prep ‚Äî positive topics, engagement indicators |
| **Ongoing Priorities** | Current work focus | 1:1 prep ‚Äî priorities table |
| **Asks from Manager** | What they need from you | 1:1 prep ‚Äî Their Asks of Me |
| **Blockers** (if present) | What's blocking them | 1:1 prep ‚Äî Blockers & Support Needed |
| **Wins** (if present) | Accomplishments | Consider for /celebrate |

#### Step 3: Present Extracted Data

```
üìã TEAMSPACE CHECK-IN ‚Äî [Name]
Date: [Today or date from check-in]

### üòä Enjoyed Last Week
- [Item 1]
- [Item 2]

### üéØ Ongoing Priorities
| Priority | Notes |
|----------|-------|
| [Priority 1] | [Any details] |
| [Priority 2] | [Any details] |

### üôã Asks from Manager
| Request | Context |
|---------|---------|
| [Ask 1] | [Details] |

